<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hi-tech Shares Sell-off Dampens HSI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell on Monday
as investors continued to sell off hi-tech stocks, following three
consecutive days of slide last week.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng index lost 513.61 points, or 2.95
percent, to close at 16,892.93, after finishing the morning
session 1.78 percent lower at 17,097.19.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 10.657 billion HK dollars (1.366 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Friday's 10.409 billion HK dollars (1.334
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All the four sub-indices dropped with Finance, Utilities,
Properties and Commerce and Industries loosing 3.18 percent, 0.29
percent, 3.45 percent and 2.92 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went down 2.77 percent and
the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporation Index lost 7.38 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
