<HEADLINE> 7 Palestinians Wounded by Israeli Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Seven Palestinian protesters were
injured when Israeli soldiers fired shots at them in Beit Amir
village, north of the West Bank town of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of Palestinians were protesting against Israeli plans
to confiscate their lands near the Jewish settlement of Karmi Tsur,
located at Halhul and Beit Amir towns. Israel plans to expand the
settlement there.
</P>
<P>
The injured were hospitalized. 
