<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Navy to Conduct Exercise With Live Ammunition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwaiti army announced
Tuesday its naval forces will conduct an exercise with live
ammunition Wednesday near the Island of UM Al-Maradem near Kuwait's
southern border with Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the army's Moral Guidance and Public
Relations Department urged people and ships to keep away from
approaching the area of the maneuver, the Kuwait News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
But the statement didn't mention whether the drill will be
joined by the United States' forces stationed here.
</P>
<P>
Currently, marines of the United States' 5th Fleet are carrying
out a joint and combined training, dubbed "Eager Mace 2000", with
Kuwaiti armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The joint Kuwaiti-U.S. war games, which started on April 1 and
will last until April 25, include amphibious, ground, air and naval
training.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said the joint exercise would also include a
mock assault on an uninhabited island to "demonstrate their
combined sea and land warfare operational capability."
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and the U.S. signed a ten-year defense cooperation
agreement after a U.S.-led multi-national force freed Kuwait from
the Iraqi occupation in February 1991.
</P>
<P>
As part of the deal, U.S. and Kuwaiti troops conducted joint war
games almost every year since 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
