<HEADLINE> LIFFE Trades 14 Trillion Pounds Worth Of Contracts For First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The London International Financial
Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) traded 14 trillion pounds for
the first quarter, maintaining its position as the largest
exchange in Europe by value.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE announced Tuesday that it traded 11,701,629 futures and
options contracts during March 2000 representing an average daily
volume of 508,766 contracts,up 3 percent on February and 19
percent on January.
</P>
<P>
Hugh Freedberg, LIFFE's Chief Executive, said: "LIFFE's
flagship Euribor contract continues to grow and is up 45 percent
year-on-year."
</P>
<P>
"Trading in equity products has increased, with the FTSE 100
index futures volume up 22 percent year-on-year and equity options
up 23 percent year-on-year," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
