<HEADLINE> Tanzania Urges EU to Help Settle African Conflicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania Tuesday urged the
European Union to support Africa in its efforts to take the
leading role and initiative in dealing with conflicts in the
continent.
</P>
<P>
In his intervention on the political issues agenda distributed
to delegates attending the Africa-Europe Summit being held in
Cairo, Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa said Europe must support
African initiatives to end its conflicts.
</P>
<P>
"In most African countries facing conflict situations,
everything else we are discussing here fades into insignificance
if people are not sure if they will be alive tomorrow," the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa noted that the socio-economic disruption brought about by
 conflicts will not only affect the country, but also its
neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
He cited the example of Tanzania with its influx of refugees
from the conflict-torn neighboring countries such as Burundi and
the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Mkapa urged the summit to support in deeds and action the
ongoing efforts in Tanzania's north town of Arusha to facilitate a
framework for sustainable peace in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
He further urged the EU to support politically and materially
the implementation of the Lusaka peace accord on the DRC conflict.
</P>
</TEXT>
