<HEADLINE> URGENT First Africa-Europe Summit Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CIARO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The first Africa-Europe summit ended
its two-day session Tuesday evening in cairo, with the issuing of a
final declaration and a plan of action.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, Algerian President Abdelaziz
Bouteflika, Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres addressed
the closing session.
</P>
<P>
The summit under the aegis of the Organization of African Unity
and the European Union (EU) covered a wide range of issues,
including trade, investment, debt, poverty relief, wars and
conflicts prevention and mine sweeping.
</P>
<P>
Heads of state or government, or their representatives from most
of the 53 African states and the 15 member countries of the
European Union (EU) attended the conference.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also agreed to hold an Africa-Europe summit every
three years, a ministerial meeting each year and an expert
gathering every six months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
