<HEADLINE> Armed Palestinian Captured North of Gaza Strip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 4 (Xinhua) -- An armed Palestinian citizen from
the Gaza Strip was captured by Israeli soldiers after a shootout
Tuesday afternoon to the north of the Strip, the Israeli Army said.
</P>
<P>
The arrested, who was wanted by the Palestinian police, tried to
infiltrate into Israel illegally with another man, the army added.
</P>
<P>
The second man turned back into the Gaza Strip and was captured
there by the Palestinian police.
</P>
<P>
Investigation into the incident is going on and it is not clear
whether the armed Palestinian was sent to Israel to carry out
terrorist activities, the army said.  
