<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Final Status Talks in Preliminary Stage: Arafat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Yasser Arafat said the Palestinian-Israeli final
status talks were still in a preliminary stage.
</P>
<P>
"None of the main topics has been resolved so far," he told
reporters after meeting visiting Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev at his presidential office in the West Bank city of
Ramallah on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We reached no solution of any of the main issues, namely
Jerusalem, refugees, settlements, water and borders," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We do not ask for the impossible, rather we want sincere and
accurate implementation of the signed accords," he added.
</P>
<P>
The meeting with the Kazakh leader covered the latest
developments of the Middle East peace process and the bilateral
relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat hailed Kazakhstan's efforts to push forward the peace
process and its long-standing support for the Palestinian cause.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nazarbayev said Kazakhstan understood the rights of
the Palestinian people to establish an independent state.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh leader appreciated Arafat's role in the Palestinian
issue, saying "your heroic role is highly appreciated worldwide and
we hope for reaching a final settlement of the question."
</P>
<P>
All the concerned parties should abide by the U.N. Security
Council resolutions to help the peace process succeed and reach its
targets, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Foreign Minister Erlan Idrisov and other senior
officials, the Kazakh leader arrived in Ramallah Tuesday morning on
a state visit to Palestine. 
</P>
