<HEADLINE> Registered Voters in Greece Stand at Over 8 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The registered voters in Greece
are 8,976,135, of which 4,593,955 are women and 4,382,180 are men,
the Macedonian Press Agency (MPA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Greece's parliamentary elections, the 10th since the
restoration of democracy in the country in 1974, will be held on
April 9 with the participation of 26 political parties, including
the ruling Panhellenic Socialist Movement (PASOK) and the main
opposition New Democracy (ND).
</P>
<P>
Currently, a total of 18,959 polling stations have been
erected throughout Greece, and the ruling PASOK-led by incumbent
Prime Minister Costas Simitis is expected to win the forthcoming
elections although it will be a close contest for the country's
two largest political parties.
</P>
