On March 14, Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos dissolved
the parliament, signalling the official start of the country's
elections campaign.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, PASOK won the country's parliamentary elections by
obtaining more than 41 percent of the votes, followed by ND with
more than 38 percent. 
