<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Innovation Key to Singapore's Future: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Singaporean Prime Minister Chok
Tong Tuesday stressed that innovation is the key to his country's
future, calling upon Singaporeans to adapt themselves to the fast-
changing new economy.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the point to the Productivity 2000
Campaign Rally attended by some 1,000 CEOs, union leaders,
representatives from employer association and productivity
activists.
</P>
<P>
Goh said the technological advances have accelerated the pace
and scale of change in the new era and the rapid spread of
knowledge has sped up the creation of new products and services
and the development of sophisticated production process.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the size of a country and distance to market are no
longer insurmountable constraints as a result of globalization, he
said a company that only looks to local suppliers for raw
materials and sells only to local customers will languish.
</P>
<P>
Winning companies look to the world market to source for the
best materials and talents, produce where it is cheapest and sell
where the demand is, he added.
</P>
<P>
Goh said through the history of mankind, countries and
corporations able to respond and adapt to changes quickly have
triumphed over others while those that failed to act and react
quickly fell by the wayside.
</P>
<P>
Goh said there is no way for Singapore to compete with labor-
abundant countries on the basis of wage costs and the only
solution for his country is to produce goods and services of a
better quality through innovation.
</P>
<P>
"The spirit of innovation must permeate every level and every
sphere of our activities", Goh said, adding the Productivity
Movement will be becoming the Productivity and Innovation Movement
with emphasis on promoting and spreading innovation and value
creation to all sectors of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Singapore's Productivity Movement was first launched in 1981
with the aim to raise productivity in every economic area and
quality of products made in the city state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
