<HEADLINE> Floods Cost S. Africa US$360 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The floods which have ravaged
large parts of South Africa since January have cost the country
about 2.2 billion rand (about 360 million U.S. dollars) in damage
to infrastructure, South African Press Association reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The above-mentioned figure is only the cost of repairing all
the damage within one financial year, South African Provincial and
Local Government Department said in a report to the National
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
