<HEADLINE> Angola, Portugal Reinforce Technical-Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Angola and
Portugal have signed a final communique to reinforce their
technical-military cooperation at the fourth meeting of their
joint commission on defense, official news agency Angop reported
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After five days of consultations in the Angolan capital Luanda,
the two sides decided to improve the training programs for
officers of the Armed Forces of Angola (FAA), the communique said.
</P>
<P>
