<HEADLINE> Philippine House Speaker Hails Latest Survey Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine House Speaker Manuel
Villar said Tuesday that the latest Social Weather Stations (SWS)
survey results showed the improved perceptions of the Estrada
administration.
</P>
<P>
The chief of the House of Representatives told reporters that
the results should inspire concerned parties to further improve
their quality of service to Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
However, Villar admitted that there is still much work to be
done, stressing the ultimate gauge of their success "is in how we
will make a positive difference in the lives of Filipinos."
</P>
<P>
The latest SWS survey showed President Joseph Estrada with a
positive 5 approval rating, indicating the president has recovered
some degree of public confidence.
</P>
<P>
It was definitely better than the negative 13 percent rating he
supposedly got in a less comprehensive survey conducted by a
pollster in February.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey results released Monday, 43 percent
were satisfied with Estrada's performance, compared with the 44
percent in December.
</P>
<P>
The president's approval ratings were stable in Metro Manila,
from negative 2 percent in last December to a positive 1 percent
in March and from positive 5 percent to positive 4 percent in
Luzon.
</P>
<P>
There was a slight decline in the Visayas, from positive 1
percent to negative 8 percent, but it was offset by an increase in
Mindanao,from positive 14 percent to positive 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The SWS' first quarter survey was undertaken on March 4 to 22
and covered 2,400 respondents.
</P>
<P>
As this developed, an opposition House member on Tuesday urged
the president's critics to give Estrada a chance to "prove his
worth."
</P>
<P>
"Resignation is much too drastic considering that the President
has only been in office for less than 2 years. Let us, in the
meantime,grant President Estrada's wish for more time to improve
his performance..." Rep. Gerardo Espina said. 
</P>
