<HEADLINE> Estrada Assures Justice for Shooting Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
vowed Tuesday to give justice to the families of victims killed in
a shooting rampage by two drunken soldiers in Oriental Mindoro
province,Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The president, who is paying a surprise visit to the town of
Victoria in Mindoro, also ordered the arrest within 72 hours of an
army sergeant who was tagged as one of the two suspects in the
killing of six persons inside a karaoke bar there.
</P>
<P>
"I will not allow these two soldiers to go scot-free," Estrada
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Estrada directed Interior Secretary Alfredo Lim and Director
General Panfilo Lacson, chief of the Philippine National Police,
to coordinate with the military in the manhunt for Marcial Ambulo,
one of the shooting suspects.
</P>
<P>
In his visit to the town, the president also personally
extended his condolences to the families of the victims in the
shooting rampage and assured them that they will get justice.
</P>
<P>
"This is a very unfortunate incident. It is unfortunate that
something like this has happened at a time our soldiers and
policemen are regaining the trust of the public," Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, Ambulo, along with Jose Rubio, who were
both drunk at the time, fired indiscriminately at customers inside
a karaoke bar in Victoria, Mindoro.
</P>
<P>
Without any provocation, the two suspects allegedly drew their.
45 caliber pistols and went on a shooting rampage, killing six
persons and wounding three others.
</P>
<P>
Rubio was arrested by responding policemen but Ambulo managed
to escape. 
</P>
