<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Tap Enormous Hydro Power Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government have
started working on feasibility studies for the construction of
more dams on its rivers to deploy the gigantic hydro power
potential in the country.
</P>
<P>
With the enormous drop in elevation of the Indus and its
tributaries, Pakistan has the potential to produce 38,000 MW hydro
power, sufficient enough to meet the power need of the country for
a long span of time, said sources with the Ministry of Water and
Power.
</P>
<P>
Feasibility reports of at least five small dams are expected to
be completed by the end of this year, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A feasibility report has already been completed to construct
small hydroelectric projects in various parts of North West
Frontier province and the Pakistan-adminsitered part of Kashmir
with total capacity of more than 3000 MW, according to a report of
the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to contact the World Bank, Asian
Development Bank and donor agencies for the funding, according to
Water and Power Ministry sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
