<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Festival to be Held in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The fifth International Tourism
Festival featuring the theme of the Three Gorges is scheduled to
open on June 8 in Chongqing Municipality in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
It will offer a series of colorful programs, including a stone
carving show, tour of the Three Gorges, which borders Chongqing
Municipality and Hubei Province, performances, exhibitions, and
local cuisine.
</P>
<P>
The festival will run concurrently with the 2000 Chongqing
Investment and Trade Talks.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 overseas companies, international economic
organizations and financial institutions are expected to
participate in these talks.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government of Chongqing will offer 400 projects
in the fields of science and technology, infrastructure, industry,
agriculture, tourism and real estate to seek investment from
abroad.
</P>
<P>
To provide convenience for domestic and foreign investors, the
city has announced an E-mail address -- ws@ft.cq.cn.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Project is aimed at damming and harnessing the
Yangtze River, the world's third-longest, in a comprehensive way.
The project has an estimated budget of 50.09 billion yuan. Upon
completion, the hydropower station is to have 26 generating units
with a combined installed capacity of 18.2 million kw and an
annual electricity output of 84.7 billion kwh, making it the
biggest hydropower station in the world. The entire project is
scheduled for completion in the year 2009. 
</P>
