<HEADLINE> Shanghai Builds Leading-Edge Information Technology Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The information technology sector
has become the top pillar industry of this east China metropolis,
said Huang Qifan, director of the Shanghai Municipal Economic
Commission, here today.
</P>
<P>
Huang told a press conference that the city's information
technology (IT) products sales reached 85 billion yuan (about 10.2
billion US dollars)-worth in 1999, up 30 percent on 1998.
</P>
<P>
He noted that this year the figure is expected to reach 100
billion yuan-worth.
</P>
<P>
Before the 1990s, the textile and automobile industries were
the economic pillars of Shanghai, he said, adding that the city's
IT products reaped profits of 4.3 billion yuan last year, up 34
percent on 1998.
</P>
<P>
A group of giant IT enterprises have emerged in the city, with
famous-brand products in the fields of software, system
application and information services.
</P>
<P>
The city will focus its IT industry on the development of
Internet connections, program-controlled telephone switchboards
and other electronic items. 
</P>
