<HEADLINE> Fair Promotes Cooperation between East And West China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China opened a high-profile trade
fair today in this capital of Shaanxi Province, in northwest China,
to step up cooperation between its prosperous eastern region and
poor western region.
</P>
<P>
The fair is the largest event to be held since Premier Zhu
Rongji announced the strategy of developing the western region at
the Third Session of the Ninth National People's Congress this
March. The move is expected to increase consumer demand and
realize all-round development.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the State Economic and Trade Commission and other
central ministries and commissions, as well as 15 major
municipalities, provinces and autonomous regions, the fair aims to
attract investment and technology to the vast western region,
which largely lags behind the other parts of the country in
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The fair has 3,500 sq m of floor space to demonstrate the
potential of the western region and how eastern cities can profit
from joining in the development of the west.
</P>
<P>
The fields of cooperation range from automobiles and energy to
machinery and high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
The fair has attracted companies from more than 20 foreign
countries, including leading transnationals such as IBM, Philips
and Siemens.
</P>
<P>
The annual fair was first launched in 1997, but ended with
small transaction volumes. Experts estimate the current one will
start a real investment rush. 
</P>
