<HEADLINE> Cabinet Reshuffle Expected Next Week: Thai PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government will conduct a
minor cabinet reshuffle next week, Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chuan told reporters after a weekly cabinet meeting that he had
personally discussed a cabinet reshuffle with leaders of the
ruling coalition parties.
</P>
<P>
He asked all coalition parties to consider changes in their
cabinet members only if necessary, as his Democrat Party will only
look for qualified candidates to replace Sanan Kachornprasart for
the posts of deputy prime minister and interior minister.
</P>
<P>
Sanan resigned from the two portfolios after the National
Counter Corruption Commission indicted him last week for
falsifying his assets and debts record.
</P>
<P>
The case is waiting for a final ruling of the Constitutional
Court.
</P>
<P>
Chuan said that he expected to complete the cabinet reshuffle
before the Songkran festival, which officially starts on April 13
and ends on April 15.
</P>
<P>
The ruling coalition must call an election of the House of
Representatives by November. 
</P>
