facilitate a new air agreement between Manila and Taipei, to
convince Taiwanese investors to bring their businesses to the
Philippines, and to attend to the concerns of some 500,000
overseas Filipino workers in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Presidential Spokesman Jerry Barican was told to
stay at his post for the time being.
</P>
<P>
"I spoke to the President last night, and the President told me
to remain in place for the time being until he is ready to make an
announcement," Barican said. 
