<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (SENSEX)
crashed by a whopping 361 points Tuesday, the second biggest
single-session fall in the history, on the Bombay Stock Exchange (
BSE) following large scale selling by foreign and domestic
institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index opened weak at 4,907.41 and
later nosedived to the day's low of 4,666.95 before closing at 4,
691.46 as against Monday's close of 5,052.94, recording a loss of
361.48 points or 7.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index tumbled by a record 202.83 points to 2,637.40
from the previous close of 2,840.23.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted sharply down at
569.34 and 217.26 compared with the previous close of 610.97 and
233.20,respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index tumbled by 124.32 points to 1,737.96 from
Monday's close of 1,862.28. 
