<HEADLINE> Major Chinese Grain Producer to Open Wider </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province, a
major grain producer, will open its agricultural sector wider to
the outside world this year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chuntao, director of the Shandong Provincial Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation Commission, said Shandong plans to
introduce more investment, agro-techniques, new crop strains, and
talented people from abroad to significantly upgrade its
traditional agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Overseas capital and advanced agro-techniques will mainly be
directed to the breeding and processing of vegetables, fruits,
fowl, aquatic products, and flowers, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
A number of investment promotion teams will soon be sent to
Europe, North America, Australia, and New Zealand, according to
Wang.
</P>
<P>
While increasing imports of grain, cotton, and soy beans, the
province, with a population of more than 80 million, will export
more vegetables, fruits, and fowl and aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
As part of this effort, the province has adopted international
standards for pollution-free agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
Shandong had a gross domestic product of 766.23 billion yuan
last year, ranking third in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
