<HEADLINE> Chinese Pay Tribute to Legendary Ancestor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of people from all
walks of life participated in activities today in the city of
Baoji to commemorate Yan Di, one of two legendary ancestors of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Baoji, in northwest China's Shaanxi Province, is believed to be
the native home of Yan Di, also known as Shennong, and today is
the Chinese Qingming Festival, an occasion for people to visit
ancestral graves.
</P>
<P>
Yan Di and Huang Di, the Yellow Emperor, are believed to be the
founders of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Local government officials and representatives of the Hong Kong
and Macao special administrative regions -- joined by Taiwan
compatriots and representatives of overseas Chinese -- bowed and
presented baskets of flowers and fruits at the Yan Di tomb.
