<HEADLINE> China's Service Sector Creates 5.71 Million Jobs Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua)-- China's rapidly growing service
sector created 5.71 million new jobs last year, accounting for 69
percent of all the nation's new jobs, according to a report issued
by the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 1.96 million people were laid-off in the
agricultural sector, while the manufacturing sector saw an
increase of 2.54 million new jobs, said the report.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1999, 192.5 million people were working in the
service sector, contributing 34.8 percent of the national GDP.
</P>
<P>
An official from the commission said that China will make
greater efforts in developing community service, domestic tourism,
education, information, and cultural and intermediary services
this year to further propel the service sector. 
</P>
