<HEADLINE> NPC Should Play Active Role, Li Peng (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, China's top legislator,
has stressed that the National People's Congress (NPC), the
country's legislative body, should play an active role in
establishing the rule of law in China.
</P>
<P>
During his recent inspection tour to China's largest industrial
and commercial city Shanghai, Li noted that the NPC should solicit
opinions and suggestions from all the circles of society in its
drive to bring into being a socialist legal system with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, on April 3 went to
the Shanghai-based Huahong-NEC Corp., the Pudong New Area, the
Shanghai Urban Planning Exhibition Hall, the Jinmao Tower, and the
Shanghai Opera House.
</P>
<P>
The Huahong-NEC Corp., a joint venture between China's Huahong
Corp.(Group) and Japan's NEC, is the country's largest and most
advanced producer of micro-electronic products.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with the company's managers and workers, Li,
also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party of China Central Committee, said that Pudong
has been developing very fast and has achieved world-renounced
progress.
</P>
<P>
To maintain development momentum, Pudong must create a better
investment environment and new management mechanisms, and
constantly increase the scientific and technological level of its
products.
</P>
