<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Claymore Mine Blast in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Three civilians were killed and 16
naval ratings were injured on Tuesday when the bus in which they
were travelling was hit by a claymore mine explosion in the
northeastern Sri Lanka, a military spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Col. R.P. Witana said the bus was attacked between
Kitulotuwa and Kantalai in the northeastern Trincomalee district.
</P>
<P>
The three persons who were killed are the bus driver, bus
conductor and a civilian employee of the navy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 16 naval ratings, 10 were admitted to Trincomalee
hospital and the other six to Dambulla hospital for treatment, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Police said the claymore mine was set off by Tamil Tiger rebels
who have been fighting for a separate homeland for minority Tamils
in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983. 
