<HEADLINE> Nigeria Announce Minor Cabinet Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A minor cabinet reshuffle has been
announced in Nigeria with the swapping of Information Minister
Dapo Sarumi and the Minister of Cooperation and Integration in
Africa Jerry Gana, said Nigerian media Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Monday in the capital Abuja by the office
of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, the swapping
of porfolios took immediate effect and the process of
handing-taking over should be completed within hours to ensure
that no vacuum is created by the changes.
</P>
<P>
The removal of Sarumi as Information Minister is widely
believed to be a first step to a mass cabinet shake-up expected
next month, one year after the inauguration of the present
government.
</P>
<P>
Gana was information minister under the former military ruler,
Ibrahim Babangida and briefly under the late Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
As new Information Minister, Gana is the chief government
spokesman to manage Nigeria's information machinery.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to his removal, Sarumi said he was not surprised at
President Olusegun Obasanjo's decision and disclosed that the
President had earlier discussed the issue with him, adding that
the redeployment was "a blessed decision" for him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
