<HEADLINE> Embezzlement Costs Ethiopian Banks $7 Million: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian banks have lost some
56 million birr (about seven million U.S. dollars) due to
embezzlement in the past three years, according to a report by
local Amharic language newspaper Addis Zemen.
</P>
<P>
The money was deceitfully loaned out to or transferred by some
20 individuals at the different times through the use of forged
documents and signatures, the report said, noting some employees
of the banks were found involved in the criminal cases.
</P>
<P>
The banks that suffered losses in the frauds include the
National Bank of Ethiopia, the Commercial Bank of Ethiopia,
Development Banks, Dashen Bank, the Awash International Bank,
Abyssinia and Wegagen banks. 
