<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Wild Fire In Bale Region Put Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The wild fire in the Bale
region, about 250 kilometers south of Addis Ababa, has been put
out completely by earlier this week, the Ethiopian Herald
newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The one-month-and-half-old fire is now completely under control
 following a fire-fighting campaign launched by more than 36,000
farmers, students and other sections of the society, the report
quoted a local official as saying.
</P>
<P>
The rains of the past few days played a considerable role in
snuffing out the fire, the officials noted.
</P>
<P>
The official said 30,250 hectares of forests and coffee
plantations, 67 residential houses and some animals were
destroyed in the fire.
</P>
<P>
A total of 215 people suspected of starting the fire have been
arrested by police, he added. Before the fire in the Bale
regions was put out, the wild fire in the Borena region,
bordering with Kenya, was also snuffed out at the end of last
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
