<HEADLINE> Angola, IMF Sign Economic Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government and the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) have signed a monitored accord
to stabilize and relaunch the economy in the southwest African
country, official news agency Angop said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to local experts, the program will help improve the
country's external credibility, its institutional capacity and
create conditions for the development of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The accord also include the improvement of the living standard
of the Angolan population, reshuffle of the country's external
debt and the access to loans for funding its economic and social
development under advantageous terms.
</P>
<P>
According to the Angolan finance minister Joaquim David and the
head of the IMF's African and Middle East division Paulo, the
accord is valid until December of this year. 
