<HEADLINE> International Flower Fair Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 China International
Flower and Horticulture Fair opened here today with the
participation of more than 200 enterprises from a dozen countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
Several enterprises from China, the United States, the
Netherlands, France, and Italy had displays of their special
flowers, hothouse equipment, and gardening machinery in the 8,000-
sq-m exhibition area of the China Agricultural Exhibition Hall.
</P>
<P>
In addition to trade negotiations, symposiums will also be held
to discuss the prospects for China's flower industry, the
protection of new plant species, and planting technology in modern
hothouses. The fair is being sponsored by the China Flower
Association.  
</P>
</TEXT>
