<HEADLINE> Wrapup: Chinese FM Spokesman's Remarks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said that apart from Beijing, the Singaporean prime minister
and his entourage will visit Xi'an, Qingdao, Shanghai and Hong
Kong as well.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question concerning the reforms of the United
Nations Security Council membership, Sun said that China is
willing to discuss the issue with other U.N. members.
</P>
<P>
He said that the U.N. should listen to the appeal of developing
countries and have thorough and in-depth discussions on the
question of Security Council reforms.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China and the European Union (EU) will resume
their talks on China's entry into the World Trade Organizations (
