<HEADLINE> Wrapup: Chinese FM Spokesman's Remarks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He noted that President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji have
sent messages to Obuchi and expressed their hopes for an early
recovery.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question concerning to President Jiang Zemin's
upcoming visit to Israel, Sun said that friendly relations of
cooperation between China and Israel are in the fundamental
interests of both peoples, and conducive to regional peace as well.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that Sino-Israeli relations of cooperation are based
on the principles of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have developed friendly cooperation in various
aspects, which will not be affected by external elements, said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
On Chinese President Jiang Zemin's upcoming visit to Egypt, the
spokesman said that Jiang will concentrate on bilateral relations
when he meets Egyptian President Muhammed Hosni Mubarak, and that
the two leaders will also talk about the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that China sincerely hopes all parties concerned in
the peace process will take a flexible, practical and serious
approach toward the negotiations on the basis of relevant U.N.
resolutions and the Land-for-Peace Principle.
</P>
<P>
China will make due efforts as a permanent member of the U.N.
Security Council to push forward the peace process, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
