<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Group of 77 Summit to be Held in Havana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Group of 77 will hold a summit
in Havana from April 10 through 14, said Cuba's ambassador to
China Alberto Rodriguez Arufe here today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first such summit since the G-77, an
organization consisting solely of developing countries, was
established 35 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said at a press conference that the summit will
focus on economic globalization, relations between the north and
the south, cooperation between developing countries, and
industrial technology.
</P>
<P>
China, though not a member, will also participate at the summit,
he said, and most member states have said they will attend,
including the leaders of about 60 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
