<DOCNO> XIE20000404.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary to Jointly Fight River Pollution with Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April, 4 (Xinhua) -- Environment protection ministers
from Hungary and its three neighboring countries, namely Romania,
Slovakia and Ukraine, met here Monday, vowing to take joint
measures to prevent the pollution of River Tissa.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the ministers agreed to make joint
investment to prevent the river from being polluted again in the
future. They also agreed to work out a plan to eliminate the
damage from the recent pollution of the river.
</P>
<P>
River Tissa, a major tributary of the Danube, was seriously
polluted this year by spills from several mine complexes in
Romania, which drew great concern from environmental groups and
some European countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
