<HEADLINE> DPRK Budget for 2000 Passes Floor of Supreme People's Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The budget of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)'s for the year 2000 passed the
floor of the country's 10th Supreme People's Assembly (SPA)
Tuesday, the Korean Central News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The budget was adopted at the third session of SPA, which
opened at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Earlier Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the session, which was attended by DPRK leader Kim Jong Il,
deputies also reviewed the implementation of the State Budget for
1999 and approved the laws adopted by the SPA presidium during its
recess, the news agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
