<DOCNO> XIE20000404.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Housing Sector Keeps Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Massive housing construction and
increasing housing sales are spurring China's economic development
and becoming a major focus of consumer spending, said a senior
official here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Vice-Minister of Construction Song Chunhua, China
has so far maintained rational and stable real estate development
nationwide, and the real estate market with ordinary housing
construction as the main element has started to pick up.
</P>
<P>
Housing construction continues to expand and sales continue to
grow, the official added.
</P>
<P>
He said the country is launching massive housing construction,
building 410 million square meters of floor space in 1999 with
total investment topping 401 billion yuan, up 19.6 percent and 11
percent, respectively, over the 1998 figures.
</P>
<P>
The booming housing sector has revived the sluggish real estate
markets, and private buyers now account for some 80 percent of
residential buyers, and this figure is still rising.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the average per capita living space of
Chinese urban residents has grown sharply to 9.6 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, fast-growing rural economic development has brought
about a boom in rural housing construction, exceeding 600 million
square meters every year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China has built three billion square
meters of rural housing over the past five years, as some five
percent of the country's total rural households built new houses
each year.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the implementation of the housing reform
nationwide, which means selling residences to citizens rather than
allocating it to them as benefits, has played an important role in
developing the housing market.
</P>
<P>
To stimulate individual spending on living quarters, the
commercial banks have launched mortgage-loan services for home
buyers Meanwhile, a housing fund-raising system targeted at
helping buyers has been effectively instituted nationwide.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
