<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Technology Used to Find Disease-Related Gene </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Scientists at the Chinese Academy
of Sciences (CAS) have used a gene-removal technology to discover
a gene related to a common respiratory disease found among newly-
born babies.
</P>
<P>
A research group at the Shanghai Institute of Cell Biology
under the CAS removed the NDST-1 gene from laboratory mice, and
after this gene was removed the mice developed the syndromes of
this respiratory distress.
</P>
<P>
Respiratory distress is a common disease among human new-borns,
and genetic studies of the mice will help scientists find cures
for this disease.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time gene-removal technology was used in
China, and it was successful after more than a year of effort by
researchers at the institute. They are now seeking further funds
to unite with foreign organizations and carry out advanced studies
in this field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
