<DOCNO> XIE20000404.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Drop in Tokyo on Profit-Taking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 132.06 points, or 0.64
percent from Monday's close to end at 20,594.93.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 18.16 points or 1.05 percent to 1,
714.29.
</P>
<P>
Profit-taking was accelerated in Tokyo by Monday's plunge in
New York's technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index, which marked
its largest one-day point loss, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 742.37 million
shares from Monday's 696.78 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Steelmaker NKK was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
While high-priced information and technology issues faced
selling, domestic demand-related issues with low- and medium-
prices continued drawing buying after the Bank of Japan's
quarterly Tankan business confidence survey underlined the
recovery trend in Japan's economy Monday, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Air transportation firms were the biggest winners, jumping 11.
86 percent as a group.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers narrowly
surpassed losers by 638 to 616, with 130 issues closing unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
