<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ivanov: Chechnya Not to Be Used For Foreign Interference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov said here Tuesday that Moscow would not allow the Chechen
issue to be used for foreign interference in its internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the breakaway republic "is too grave and
painful a problem for anyone to try to speculate on it," Ivanov
said at a meeting with U.N. High Commissioner for Human Rights
Mary Robinson.
</P>
<P>
The minister accused certain foreign circles of trying to
present the federal operation in Chechnya "as a struggle against
Islam, the Chechen people and even as an action ahead of the
Russian presidential elections even without trying to understand
the roots of the problem," the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Russian side is ready "to resolve the Chechen problem
openly, in cooperation with the international community," Ivanov
said.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia has recently accommodated trips to the North
Caucasus for a large number of international organizations.
</P>
<P>
Robinson's trip to Dagestan, Ingushetia and Chechnya, "just as
the visits of representatives of other international organizations,
is called upon to show that we do not intend to hide anything,"
Ivanov said.
</P>
<P>
Robinson, who arrived here last week on a working visit, had
complained that she was not able to visit all the places she
wanted, complaints refuted by Russian officials accompanying her.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Kalamanov, the Russian presidential human rights envoy
to the breakaway republic, said Monday that Russia was unable to
organize a visit to Katyr-Yurt because it had not been put on the
itinerary for her trip to the breakaway republic.
</P>
<P>
He described Robinson's claim as a "common lie," complaining of
her biased stance on Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
"As I said, it would be very difficult to restore the Chechens'
trust, but why is such mistrust is displayed by the high
commissioner?" he asked.
</P>
<P>
"When we talk with Mrs. Robinson one-on-one, no problems arise.
As soon as Mrs. Robinson's suite appears, she immediately changes,
" Kalamanov said, noting that he was confused by Robinson's
behavior.
</P>
<P>
Hypocrisy as regards the issue of Chechnya must be removed in
relations between Russia and the West, Kalamanov said.
</P>
<P>
Robinson is expected to present her report on Chechnya at a U.N.
Commission for Human Rights conference on April 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
