<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Improves Business Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province, which
faces Taiwan across the Taiwan Straits, will step up efforts to
improve its business environment this year.
</P>
<P>
Xi Jinping, Fujian provincial governor, said that local
government staff will be reduced by about a half to increase
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
New laws and regulations will be drafted, Xi said, adding that
all outdated and irrational rules and regulations concerning
overseas investment in the province will be abolished.
</P>
<P>
According to the governor, the province has already established
a special working group to coordinate the effort to sort out
related rules and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three months, the province has dropped off 333
irrational rules and regulations in the field, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has approved a total of 26,281 overseas-funded
enterprises, with a combined overseas investment of 30.24 billion
U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
