<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Closes Down Half of Small Coal Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 4 (Xinhua)-- Southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has closed down over 1,000 small coal mines,
accounting for more than one half of its small coal mines.
</P>
<P>
In Laibing County, 95 out of its 211 small coal mines have been
shut down, while a group of 20 technicians patrol the remaining
mines to spot danger signs and prevent accidents.
</P>
<P>
Small coal mines, which are often improperly licensed, have
been the scene of frequent accidents in the past few years,
experts said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the closing down of small mines is a way of
reducing national coal output in the face of declining market
conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
