<HEADLINE> Beijing Creates Tulip Garden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's largest tulip garden has
been created in Beijing's eastern suburbs following the
importation of bulbs from the Netherlands in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The garden occupies an area of 26 hectares and has over one
million tulips of many colors. The garden will formally open to
visitors on April 15.
</P>
<P>
Jinzhan township has invested over 48.7 million yuan in the
garden, which also has lakes, ponds and windmills, all typical of
the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
So far, the garden has sold 80,000 fresh cut tulips and 100,000
potted flowers in Beijing.  
</P>
