<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Those Going Against People's Will Be Doomed to Failure: Commentary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's official news agency
Xinhua today released a commentary on the stepping down of Taiwan'
s Lee Teng-hui, noting that those going against the will of the
people will come to no good.
</P>
<P>
As a politician who was a master at playing with public opinion,
Lee has ironically lost all public support, and was forced to
announce his resignation following protests.
</P>
<P>
"It's quite natural that Lee has eventually come to a
disgraceful end," the commentary noted.
</P>
<P>
Lee has betrayed the common wishes and aspirations of people on
both sides of the Taiwan Straits for improved cross-Straits
relations, it said.
</P>
<P>
Peace, stability, and development are the common wishes of the
Taiwan people, who have called for cross-Straits dialogue and
political talks aimed at ending the hostile atmosphere on the two
sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
However, since he came to office, Lee has been bent on the
promotion of Taiwan's separation from the motherland, incessantly
challenging the principle of one China, and undermining cross-
Straits relations, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
Lee also took steps to thwart the development of economic and
trade relations between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits, while
turning a deaf ear to the call of the people of Taiwan for direct
links in trade, transportation, and postal services as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
"Lee's perverse acts have aroused cries of discontent all
across the island," the commentary said.
</P>
</TEXT>
