provide any credit guarantees for the 5-million-U.S.-dollar Akkuyu
Nuclear Power Plant project until the end of 2000 and not review it
for the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
This move meant that the bid for the project in southern Turkey,
which has been delayed several times, might be cancelled.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Energy Ministry is planning to take
the "Build-Operate-Transfer" (BOT) model for the construction of
the plant.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning):
</P>
<P>
-- The inflation rate in March, for the first time in 13 months,
dropped under 3 percent in Turkey, according to figures of the
State Statistics Institute on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In March, the wholesale price index (TEFE) increased by 3.1
percent, and consumer price index (TUFE) by 2.9 percent, compared
to 4.0 percent and 4.1 percent respectively in the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The yearly inflation rate in the TEFE was estimated at 66.1
percent and TUFE at 67.9 percent. 
