<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cargo Transport on China-Viet Nam Railway Sets Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Cargo transport on the China-Viet
Nam Railway reached 79,286 tons in the first three months this
year, up 20 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Kunming Railway Administration, freight
transport on the route has developed rapidly since it reopened in
1996 when it only handled less than 50,000 tons of cargo.
</P>
<P>
But now, five pairs of freight trains are running this route
from opposite direction with transport volume hitting a record
high in the first quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the railway transported 318,973 tons of cargo along
the route, 6.8 times more than that of four years ago.
</P>
<P>
The variety of goods transported has also been expanded to
include fertilizers and tobacco products along with the
traditional building materials shipped on the line.
</P>
<P>
Shanyao, a railway port in Yunnan linking China and Viet Nam,
shoulders the heavy task of transporting goods to and from both
sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
