<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Benefits from Foreign Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
which ranks third in the country in gross domestic product, has
benefited a great deal from some 12,500 foreign experts employed
by the province over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
With the help of these experts, Shandong has developed an
increasing number of high-tech products, including cloned rabbits
and industrial robots.
</P>
<P>
In the city of Weifang, a major vegetable producer, about 100
foreign experts have introduced more than 70 new strains of
vegetables from other countries.
</P>
<P>
At the Haier Group, a leading Chinese household electric
appliances manufacturer which exports its products to over 35
countries, foreign technicians and managerial experts are engaged
in all major divisions of the company.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government said that employing
foreign expert is part of Shandong's effort to bring its
technological development to an advance level.
</P>
<P>
Foreign experts are now mostly active in the province's
agricultural and industrial sectors, the official said, adding
that they will be directed to a wider range of areas in the years
to come.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
