<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hinterland Province Seeks Cooperation with Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province,
in a bid to speed up its development, tries to get more help from
the country's financial center of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The province has signed 11 contracts with the Municipality
since last October with a number of others under negotiations. The
cooperation relates electricity transmitting, textile technology,
trading of cotton yarn, and cigarette paper production.
</P>
<P>
A delegation led by Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi is invited to
visit Zhengzhou, capital of Henan, this month, discussing further
cooperation between the two places.
</P>
<P>
Henan is the country's most populous province with some 93
million people. It is home to 121 mineral resources, of which, 48
are among the top reserves in China.
</P>
<P>
Henan is of abundant tourism resources as it is one of the
birthplaces of Chinese culture, and location of capitals of more
than 20 dynasties in history.
</P>
<P>
It also serves as an important railway transportation hub and
the largest transfer station for both passengers and cargo. The
newly opened Asian-European Railway, linking east China's
Lianyungang with Holland in Europe, runs across the whole
province.
</P>
<P>
Henan's great potentials have attracted investors from Shanghai
who own technology and capital and are looking for stable raw
material suppliers and bigger market for their products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
