<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar Marks 10th Anniversary of Hong Kong Basic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A seminar attended by more than
100 law experts and governmental officials from Hong Kong and
inland areas was held here to mark today's 10th anniversary of the
promulgation of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed that the implementation of this law is
fundamental to the long-term development, prosperity and stability
of the special administrative region after its return to the
motherland in 1997.
</P>
<P>
They recalled the history of the law's birth and implementation,
saying that as a national law, it has great influence not only in
Hong Kong, but nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The seminar also discussed new questions arising during the law
's implementation such as judicial jurisdiction and legal
applications.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was jointly sponsored by the People's University of
China and the Law Institute of the City University of Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
