<HEADLINE> Chinese Army Sets up Anti-Disaster Units </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) has established 18 special fast-reaction units to fight
natural disasters, according to army sources.
</P>
<P>
The emergency units, which are part of the PLA's engineering
corps, are the first of its kind in the army history, and they
will be responsible for combating natural disasters in areas along
the country's major rivers and lakes.
</P>
<P>
While continuing their military training, these troops will
also be engaged in training to fight many kinds of natural
disasters. The PLA headquarters plans to build these units into
powerful task forces within three to five years.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, PLA troops have been widely used in combating
natural disasters, winning great appreciation from everyone for
their brave and effective battles against floods and earthquakes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
