<HEADLINE> Malaysia Adopting Approaches To Rebut Negative Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is adopting varying
approaches in disseminating information about the country abroad
depending on the targeted audience to rebut negative reports by
the foreign media, Foreign Minister Syed Hamid Albar said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Despite the different approaches, the action has been taken in
an integrated one, he told parliament, adding that it's not just
in reaction to a particular issue.
</P>
<P>
He said all Malaysian diplomatic missions abroad were supplied
with the latest updates on national policies as well as on
economic, social and political developments designed to keep
foreigners as well as Malaysians abroad abreast with current
affairs in the country and to rebut negative reports by the
foreign media.
</P>
<P>
The missions are also regularly supplied with Malaysian
newspapers for distribution among Malaysians abroad besides e-mail
and website items, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad during his trips abroad
had never missed any opportunity to meet Malaysians and keep them
updated on development back at home.
</P>
<P>
Syed Hamid said such approach did bring about positive results
as far as the targeted audience was concerned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
