<DOCNO> XIE20000404.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Capable of Heading U.N. Peacekeepers in E.Timor: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is confident that
its armed forces have the capacity to head the U.N. Peacekeeping
Force in East Timor in view of its wide experience and
professionalism, Foreign Minister Syed Hamid Albar said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
East Timor Revolutionary Council leader Xanana Gusmao said
during his visit to Malaysia in early February that the head of
the peacekeeping force could be rotated among the ASEAN countries
and proposed that Malaysia be chosen to head the force after the
Philippines, Syed Hamid told parliament.
</P>
<P>
He said Xanana Gusmao expressed the wish for more Malaysian
soldiers in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is ready to send more peacekeepers to East Timor if
requested by the United Nations and if agreeable to the leaders of
East Timor, he added.
</P>
<P>
At present, Malaysia has only 20 military observers in East
Timor, who are under the United Nations Transitional
Administration in East Timor and are also working as liaison
officers and interpreters between the local people and the
peacekeepers, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
