<HEADLINE> Chechen Rebels Reportedly Kill All Police Captives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Federal Security
Service (FSB) said Tuesday that Chechen rebels executed all nine
elite policemen they captured earlier last week in Zhani-Vedeno in
southern Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
The executions took place Sunday, the FSB public relations
center said, citing convincing information, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The center said the FSB, the main successor to the Soviet KGB,
had received information convincingly exposing a planned
provocation of supporters of field commanders Khattab and Shamil
Basayev to feign the exchange of the policemen.
</P>
<P>
As many as 43 federal soldiers and policemen were reportedly
killed last week in a deadly ambush by the rebels
</P>
<P>
The militants, in an alleged official statement on the Internet,
suggested an exchange of nine Russian elite OMON policemen
captured in combat near Zhani-Vedeno for a Russian colonel
recently arrested on charges of raping and killing a Chechen woman.
</P>
<P>
They had threatened to shoot all the nine policemen if the
proposal was not accepted.
</P>
<P>
The FSB said the executions were designed to "paint the federal
command in a negative light as persons unwilling to rescue their
own men from the hands of militants."
</P>
<P>
According to intercepted radio communications between Khattab,
a Jordanian national fighting alongside the Chechens, and Khabib,
another Arab fighter, Khattab said: The situation was very
difficult and we killed them, the FSB said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
