<HEADLINE> Shanghai Police Uncover First Internet Porn Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai police said today they
have arrested a man suspected of spreading porn on the Internet,
the first Internet porn case uncovered in the Chinese financial
center.
</P>
<P>
Initial police investigations reveal that Shang Xinjun, an
employee with the Wenhua Technological Co., Ltd. in Xi'an, capital
of northwest China's Shaanxi Province, placed 33 pornographic
pictures on a homepage at a Shanghai-funded website: www.myrice.
com. The website attracted more than 1.45 million surfers in the
past few months.
</P>
<P>
Shang was also found to have had connections with overseas porn
websites. He said he spread pornography on the Net to attract
advertisements.  
