<HEADLINE> Yunnan to Develop "Green Economy" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Province in southwest China
will make great effort to develop "green economy" in the next five
to 10 years, making full use of its rich biological resources.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shouzhi, deputy secretary of the Yunnan provincial
government, said that Yunnan will make "green economy" an
important force to promote local economy.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is also spokesman of the provincial government, is
here to attend the Fourth China East-West Cooperation and
Investment Trade Fair, scheduled for April 5-9.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan, known as "kingdom of animals and plants", boasts of 18,
000 kinds of advanced plants, over 2,000 kinds of traditional
Chinese herbal medicines, and 365 kinds of spice plants.
</P>
<P>
It also has 1,638 kinds of vertebrate animals and 10,000 kinds
of insects. These animals and plants scattered around Dianchi Lake,
Xishuangbanna in southern Yunnan and in scenic spots along Lancang,
Nujiang and Jinsha rivers in the northwestern part of the province.
</P>
<P>
The local government will adopt advanced scientific method to
develop pollution-free industries and to improve environment in a
bid to achieve coordinated development of population, resources,
environment and society, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Yunnan is building a large biological resources
development base which will concentrate on the production of
flowers, natural drugs, health food, coffee, banana and tea.
</P>
<P>
Flowers produced in Kunming, the provincial capital, contribute
to one-third of the country's total output and are sold to Macao,
Hong Kong, Singapore, Thailand, and Japan.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day trade fair in Xi'an, capital of northwest
Shaanxi Province, Yunnan will hold business promotion activities
for 280 projects which cover infrastructure facilities, tourism,
forestry and agriculture sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
