<HEADLINE> NBA Suspends, Fines Childs, Bryant for Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The NBA Monday suspended New
York Knicks guard Chris Childs for two games and Los Angeles
Lakers guard Kobe Bryant one game for fighting during Sunday's
game in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
NBA Vice presideng Rod Thorn said Childs instigated the fight
and threw punches during Sunday's nationally televised game.
Bryant was disciplined for responding with a punch.
</P>
<P>
Childs was suspended without pay for two games and fined 15,000
US dollars. Bryant was suspended without pay for one game, which
based on his 9-million-dollar salary for the season will cost him
100,000 dollars, and fined 5,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The incident occured with 43 seconds left in the third quarter
of the Lakers' 106-82 rout of New York. The pair got into a
shoving match that escalated with Childs punching Bryant in the
jaw. Both players received double technicals for fighting and were
ejected.
</P>
<P>
Childs will sit out Thursday's game at Washington and Friday's
contest in Orlando. Bryant is to miss the Lakers' game at Phoenix
Tuesday. 
