<HEADLINE> Thailand's Population Stands at 61 million: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 4 (Xinhua) -- An official survey has put
Thailand's population at 61,661,701, the Bangkok Post reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by the local administration department of
the Interior Ministry, said that out of the total recorded at the
end of December last year, 30,650,172 are men.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, Bangkok has 5.6 million residents, but
officially perhaps twice that number live in the capital city, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Nakon Ratchasima in the northeast is the only province after
Bangkok with a population more than two million. Southern province
Ranong has the smallest population of only 158,185. 
</P>
