<HEADLINE> Beijing to Choose Policemen Among College Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The public security department in
the Chinese capital will recruit about 200 new policemen among
this year's college graduates, as a measure to improve the quality
of the police contingent of 43,000 policemen in the city.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the local public security bureau said that
college graduates or those with even higher educational level,
regardless of their major, are welcome to make applications for
the job if they are determined to engage in public security.
</P>
