<HEADLINE> China Builds Data Banks of Geological Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China has started to build the
country's largest basic geological information system with a group
of data banks.
</P>
<P>
The system, to be completed in 2008, will include data banks
of 1:50,000 digital grid maps, core topographical maps, geographic
names, digital altitude model maps, land-cover maps and other data
banks.
</P>
<P>
This geological information system is expected to meet the
future demands of China's social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
It will provide basic materials for planning of regional
development, development of resources, environmental protection,
geological survey and building of water conservation projects.
</P>
<P>
The 1:50,000 data bank will form the framework of a national
geospace data system with a 1:1 million map data bank, a 1:250,
000 map data bank and some other data banks.
</P>
<P>
Experts here believed that building of the basic geological
information system will also push ahead the digital technological
upgrading of the mapping industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
