<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Builds Magnetic Materials Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The first-phase project of a
magnetic materials industrial park, involving a total investment
of 680 million yuan, is under construction in Dongyang City, in
east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The park will house 57 high-tech magnetic enterprises and a 21-
storey mansion, and will engage in the production of high-tech
magnetic materials mainly for the electronic industry.
</P>
<P>
The magnetic materials sector is a pillar industry for Dongyang.
The small city has now nearly 200 enterprises that turn out the
products. Hengdian Group, the leader among these enterprises, is
the world's largest permanent ferrite production base, with its 80
percent of its products sold to more than 30 countries and regions,
including the United States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Construction work on the park, fully invested by Hengdian Group
which is known as "China's Magnetic Capital", will be completed in
three years.  
</P>
