<DOCNO> XIE20000404.0314 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Publish Dictionary on Xixia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China is to publish a dictionary
on Xixia, a kingdom established in the 11th century by a number of
ethnic groups in what is now Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region in
northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The dictionary will be the largest of its kind concerning
research on the Xixia kingdom which covered Ningxia, Gansu,
Qinghai and part of Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. The kingdom
was conquered by the Yuan Dynasty in 1227.
</P>
<P>
Xixia was usually considered as a "mysterious kingdom" because
very few historical records on the kingdom remained. So, this
dictionary will be helpful for a systematic study on the subject,
experts in the field said.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 Chinese scholars have gathered recently in
Yinchuan, capital of Ningxia, to discuss issues concerning the
editing and publishing of the dictionary, which is due to be
published in 2002 . 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
