<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- An agricultural technology
exposition will be held November 5-9 in Yangling, the country's
only state-level agricultural high-tech demonstration zone, in
Shaanxi Province, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, the seventh of its kind, is jointly sponsored
by the provincial government of Shaanxi and 16 departments of the
central government, including the Ministry of Science and
Technology.
</P>
<P>
The event will display the achievements and products of China's
agricultural technology in an effort to attract domestic and
overseas investment, further develop China's western areas,
improve environmental construction, and promote exchanges and
cooperation in agricultural high-tech developments, according to
an official with the organizing committee.
</P>
