<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Urges Israel to Punish Killers of 2 Jordanians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Jordan has urged Israel to punish the
suspected killers of two Jordanians in an explosion at a hotel in
the Israeli port city of Eilat 10 days ago, Foreign Minister Abdel
Ilah al-Khatib said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian government has officially requested Israel to
inform the kingdom of the outcome of the ongoing investigations
into the case in which Mohammad Abdullah Yassin and Murad Abdel
Karim were killed at the Etzion Hotel on March 26.
</P>
<P>
Both victims were Jordanian nationals but had been working
illegally in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Israel said that police have arrested three Israeli
suspects who were believed to have masterminded the explosion over
an alleged money dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli side believed there are some 40,000 Jordanians
living or working illegally in the Jewish state, mostly in cities
and towns with a significant Arab population.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Israel signed a historical peace treaty in 1994, but
no agreement on the movement of labor force between the two
countries has been signed.
</P>
<P>
However, the two countries signed a minor and pilot agreement
last month, under which Israel will permit daily 200 Jordanians
from Jordan's southern port city of Aqaba to cross the border and
work in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The project is set to begin by the end of April or early May,
and Israeli officials said if the project goes well, it will be
expanded to other areas of Jordan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000404.0344 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Wants to Forge Strategic Partnership With Africa: Portuguese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) wants to "
establish a new strategic partnership" with Africa through the
first Africa-Europe summit, a Portuguese official said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We, Europeans, do not want to get anything from Africa except
establishment of a new partnership to promote the governance and
stability of Africa," Neviz Fernandos, spokesman for the Portuguese
delegation, told Xinhua after the end of the summit.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day summit under the aegis of the EU and the
Organization of African Unity, leaders of 67 African and EU
countries discussed economic, political and social issues in Africa
and seek close cooperation between the two regions in tackling the
issues.
</P>
<P>
Portugal is currently holding EU's rotating presidency.
</P>
<P>
Fernandos, meanwhile, said development and stability in Africa
will be attained through the actions and efforts of the Africans
themselves.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the significance of the summit, he said it lies in
the sheer fact that it has taken place. The participation of EU
countries in the summit demonstrated their interest in and
commitment to Africa, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the summit, some countries announced to contribute to the
debt relief process, Fernandos said.
</P>
<P>
Germany has said it would write off 350 million U.S. dollars of
debts of some poor countries. France and Morocco have also
announced to write off debts of a number of poor countries in
coming years.
</P>
<P>
The summit has established a new institutionalized process which
will be fruitful and lead to better relations between the two
continents and improvement of governance in Africa, the Portuguese
official said.
</P>
<P>
The African and EU countries have decided to create a follow-up
mechanism with further summits "based on the principle of
continuity," the next one to be held in Europe in 2003, with a
meeting of ministers in between. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
