<HEADLINE> Romania's Central Bank Consolidates International Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Romania's Central Bank's process
of consolidating its hard currency reserves continued in March,
which are worth 1,632.5 million U.S. dollars, up 67.3 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold reserve amounted to 103.6 tons but its value
diminished to 919.2 million U.S. dollars because of the evolution
of international prices.
</P>
<P>
Thus, the international reserves (hard currency plus gold) are
worth over 2.5 billion U.S. dollars in Romania's Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
Until the end of the year, payments which are due on account of
domestic in hard currency and foreign public debt are of 998
million U.S. dollars. Out of this debt, guaranteed by the Romanian
Finance Ministry, hard currency T-bonds issued in the domestic
market are worth 186 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank continues to consolidate its reserves and to
ensure the service of foreign public debt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
